\cf2 /* in the above, a pulse is used to gate a sinewave -- but it creates a click, so a better method is to use and Impulse input to Decay2, which creates a simple decaying Envelope that will round off the attack and provide a variable-length decay -- \
Decay2.ar(in, attackTime, decayTime, mul, add)\
Decay2 is essentially a 2nd order filter (2 sample delay), with the filter co-efficients calculated for you to produce the attack/decay characteristics you specify. \
In the next example, an Impulse is input to the Decay2 filter, which is multiplied (enveloped) by the sinewave to create a decaying 'ping' -- play around with the arguments here, and you can create some very effective percussion instruments\
*/\cf0 \
\{ \cf3 Decay2\cf0 .ar(\cf3 Impulse\cf0 .ar(4,0,0.25), \
			0.01, 0.2, \cf3 FSinOsc\cf0 .ar(600)) \}.play;\
\
\{ \cf3 Decay2\cf0 .ar(\cf3 Impulse\cf0 .ar(4,0,0.25), \
			0.01, 0.2, \cf3 WhiteNoise\cf0 .ar(0.1)) \}.play;\
